com.vector.cfg.model.access

Class ModelAccessUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vector.cfg.model.access.ModelAccessUtil

  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public final class ModelAccessUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides some static utility methods which shall be published for internal and external generators.

    ModelAccessUtil

    The class ModelAccessUtil is a static utility class. It provides some very basic methods which are sometimes useful in client code and for debugging. The most important are:
    • #getProjectContext(MIObject): Returns the IProjectContext the specified MIObject corresponds to
    • #toDebugStringMDFObject(MIObject): Returns a string representation of the specified object and its content to support debugging

    Important remark: Do not change or add something here without discussing your requirements with the responsible PLD of the model plugin! In general, the policy for providing static utility methods shall be: Use project services instead if possible. The are more flexible and can easily be mocked.

      • ensureIsVisible

        @PublishedMethod
public static void ensureIsVisible(MIObject object)
        Ensures, that the passed MIObject is currently visible and not removed.

        Otherwise this method will throw either an InvisibleVariantObjectException, if invisible, or an ModelCeAlreadyRemovedException, if removed.

        Parameters:
        object - is the object to be checked
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException -
        • if the element is null
        InvisibleVariantObjectException -
        • if the element is invisible
        ModelCeAlreadyRemovedException -
        • if the element is removed
